The quokka ( , Setonix brachyurus ) , the only member of the genus Setonix , is a small macropod about the size of a domestic cat .
Like other marsupials in the macropod family ( such as kangaroos and wallabies ) , the quokka is herbivorous and mainly nocturnal .
Quokkas are found on some smaller islands off the coast of Western Australia , particularly Rottnest Island , just off Perth , and also Bald Island near Albany , and in isolated scattered populations in forest and coastal heath between Perth and Albany .
A small colony exists at the eastern limit of their range in a protected area of Two Peoples Bay Nature Reserve , where they co - exist with the critically endangered Gilbert 's potoroo .
